  "text": "## LLVM Pass Manager Registration and Execution Chain\n\n### 1. PassManager Template Architecture\n\nThe core PassManager is defined in `llvm/include/llvm/IR/PassManager.h` as a template class `PassManager<IRUnitT, AnalysisManagerT, ExtraArgTs>`. Two key typedefs are:\n- **ModulePassManager**: `PassManager<Module>` for module-level passes\n- **FunctionPassManager**: `PassManager<Function>` for function-level passes\n\n### 2. Pass Registration Pipeline\n\n**PassRegistry** (`llvm/include/llvm/PassRegistry.h` and `llvm/lib/IR/PassRegistry.cpp`) is the global registry system:\n- `PassRegistry::getPassRegistry()` returns the global singleton instance\n- `registerPass()` stores PassInfo objects in PassInfoMap and PassInfoStringMap\n- Passes are registered with metadata defined in `llvm/include/llvm/PassInfo.h`\n\nPass metadata is defined using macro-based declarations in `llvm/lib/Passes/PassRegistry.def`, which includes:\n- MODULE_PASS: Module transformation passes (e.g., \"always-inline\", \"globalopt\")\n- MODULE_ANALYSIS: Module-level analyses (e.g., \"callgraph\", \"lcg\")\n- FUNCTION_PASS: Function-level passes\n- Corresponding analysis entries\n\n### 3. Pass Addition Mechanism\n\nThe `addPass()` method in `PassManager` (line 193-201 of PassManager.h):\n- Takes a templated pass object\n- Wraps it in a PassModelT concrete type\n- Stores it in a `std::vector<std::unique_ptr<PassConceptT>>` called `Passes`\n- Enables runtime polymorphism using the concept-based design pattern\n\n### 4. Pass Execution Order\n\nThe `run()` method in `llvm/include/llvm/IR/PassManagerImpl.h` (lines 27-98) implements the execution sequence:\n1. Retrieves PassInstrumentation from AnalysisManager\n2. Iterates through `Passes` vector in order\n3. For each pass:\n   - Calls `PI.runBeforePass()` for instrumentation callbacks\n   - Executes `Pass->run(IR, AM, ExtraArgs...)` \n   - Invalidates analyses via `AM.invalidate(IR, PassPA)`\n   - Calls `PI.runAfterPass()` for post-execution callbacks\n   - Intersects preserved analyses with aggregate set\n\n### 5. Standard Optimization Pipeline (O2/O3)\n\nThe pipeline is constructed via **PassBuilder** (`llvm/include/llvm/Passes/PassBuilder.h` and `llvm/lib/Passes/PassBuilder.cpp`):\n\n**Main Entry Point**: `buildPerModuleDefaultPipeline()` in PassBuilderPipelines.cpp (line 1716)\n- Selects appropriate pipeline based on OptimizationLevel (O0, O1, O2, O3, Os, Oz)\n- For O2/O3, builds a ModulePassManager by combining:\n  1. `buildModuleSimplificationPipeline()` (line 1091) - Adds early optimization passes\n  2. `buildModuleOptimizationPipeline()` (line 1478) - Adds main optimization passes\n\n**Simplification Pipeline** includes (from line 1091):\n- Inference of function attributes (InferFunctionAttrsPass)\n- Early function optimizations (EntryExitInstrumenterPass, SimplifyCFGPass, SROAPass, EarlyCSEPass)\n- OpenMP and interprocedural optimizations (IPSCCPPass, CalledValuePropagationPass, GlobalOptPass)\n- PGO instrumentation if enabled\n- Early loop passes and inline preparation\n\n**Optimization Pipeline** includes (from line 1478):\n- Loop transformations (LoopRotatePass, LoopDeletionPass, LoopInterchangePass)\n- Vectorization passes via `addVectorPasses()` (line 1610)\n- Control Height Reduction for O3 (line 1565)\n- Late scalar optimizations (LoopSinkPass, InstSimplifyPass, DivRemPairsPass)\n- Inlining passes (ModuleInlinerPass or ModuleInlinerWrapperPass)\n\nKey O3-specific features:\n- CallSiteSplittingPass for O3 only (line 1151)\n- ControlHeightReductionPass for O3 only (line 1565)\n- Additional loop unrolling and vectorization tuning\n\n### 6. Execution Flow Summary\n\nThe complete execution chain:\n```\nPassBuilder::buildPerModuleDefaultPipeline()\n  ↓\nModulePassManager MPM\n  ↓\nMPM.addPass(buildModuleSimplificationPipeline(...))\n  ↓\nMPM.addPass(buildModuleOptimizationPipeline(...))\n  ↓\nMPM.run(Module &IR, AnalysisManager &AM)\n  ↓\nFor each pass in Passes:\n  - Pass->run(IR, AM) executes the pass\n  - AM.invalidate(IR, PassPA) updates analysis state\n```\n\nEach pass returns a `PreservedAnalyses` bitset indicating which analyses remain valid, allowing the AnalysisManager to avoid recomputing analyses across the pipeline while maintaining correctness."
